Value: a falcivax rapid diagnostic test that occurs in a hospital facility

Subject: information on whether antimalarial treatment initiated
Value: a categorical value specification that specifies whether a human participant under investigation is receiving treatment to alleviate symptoms of malaria

Subject: subnational region visited within past month
Value: human traveling information that specifies which subnational regions a human participant under investigation had visited within one month previous

Subject: information on whether fourth antimalarial taken
Value: a categorical value specification that specifies whether a human participant under investigation was administered malaria medication a fourth time while in hospital

Subject: information on whether fifth antimalarial taken
Value: a categorical value specification that specifies whether a human participant under investigation was administered malaria medication a fifth time while in hospital

Subject: subnational region visited within past 12 months
Value: human traveling information that specifies which subnational regions a human participant under investigation had visited within twelve months previous

Subject: treatment start date
Value: a time measurement datum of the date during which a treatment starts

Subject: treatment start time
Value: a time measurement datum of the time point at which a treatment starts

Subject: 60-day follow-up observation time
Value: a time measurement datum specifying the time (of day) of a clinical visit scheduled for sixty days after a treatment

Subject: blood bilirubin concentration
Value: a scalar measurement datum of the mass concentration of bilirubin in blood that is a specified output of a blood test

Subject: information on participant travel in the last twelve months
Value: a categorical value specification that is about a human participant under investigation and specifies whether the participant had traveled within twelve months previous

Subject: information on whether participant is member of tribe
Value: a categorical value specification that specifies whether a human participant under investigation self-identifies as a member of a tribe

Subject: information on whether participant died in hospital
Value: a categorical value specification that specifies whether the life-death temporal boundary of a human participant under investigation occurred during a health care encounter in a hospital facility
